notesStmt.note: Title supplied by cataloger; titles of component parts from table of contents (p. 1).

msContents.summary: Collection of Persian poetry with an introductory table of contents by Saʻīd Nafīsī, a former owner (p.1). Several leaves copied by Nafīsī and inserted. They include two poems by Ḥāfiẓ (p. 156); 12 pages containing poems from the margins of a copy of Khusraw Dihlavī (p.197b-197l); and two poems missing from the Dīvān of Ḥakīm Tirmiz̲ī (unnumbered page after p. 259).

author.persName: Ibn Yamīn, Fakhr al-Dīn Maḥmūd, 1287 or 1288-1367 or 1368
ابن يمين، فخر الدين محمود، 1287 or 1288-1367 or 1368
Ḥakīm Tirmiz̲ī, Muḥammad ibn ʻAlī, active 9th century
Busḥāq Aṭʻimah Shīrāzī, Ḥallāj, active 15th century

msItem.title: Muntakhab-i mas̲navīyāt-i Khusraw Dihlavī va Niẓāmī

supportDesc.extent: i, 180 paginated leaves : 233 x 140 (175 x 90) mm, bound to 235 x 140 mm

layoutDesc.layout: 21 long lines; chiefly in two columns; no catchwords; border-ruled.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed; headings in thuluth; pointed and vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated headpiece in gold and colors (p. 61, 199); polychrome illuminated headers with leaf and vine motifs (p. 1, 125, 157, 305); textblock border-ruled in blue and red or blue and gold; columns and sections ruled in red; rubrications in red, green, blue, gold; some poetry set off by red markers.

binding.p: Light brown leather faintly blind-stamped with central mandorla, six pendants, four on the vertical axis and two on the horizontal, and cornerpieces; blind-tooled double frame; plain paper doublure.

origin.p: Copy completed in Muḥarram 836 AH (1432 CE) by ʻAlī ibn Ḥakīm Tirmiz̲ī (p. 240).

history.provenance: Forms part of the Saʻīd Nafīsī collection purchased by Columbia Unversity in 1961 (library bookplate inside back cover).
Sold by Mīrzā ʻAlī Aṣghar Kitābfurūsh [bookseller] to Saʻīd Nafīsī in Tehran in Ābān 1314 (October 1935 CE) (note in ink, p. 200 [=0])
Formerly owned by Saʻīd Nafīsī, number 3494 (stamp and note in ink, p. 200 [=0])
